  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>Macular sensitivity</measure>
    <time_frame>12 months</time_frame>
    <description>The objective of this study was to assess macular function by measuring its sensitivity using microperimetry in patients with idiopathic ERM every three months up to one year. We compared the results of macular sensitivity to the best-corrected visual acuity (BCVA) and the OCT data to better understand the structure-function relationship.</description>
